\f0\fs24 \cf0 This code will calculate the sulfur content at sulfide saturation (SCSS) values for a given set of melt compositions and a specified pressure using the O\'92Neill (2019) model.\
\
Simply run the code multiple times on the same input file if you wish to calculate the SCSS at different pressure intervals for a given set of melt compositions.\
\
The code is written in python and can be used from the command terminal on a Mac.\
\
